Project overview 

The Library Management System (LMS) is a software application designed to manage the operations of a library efficiently. It helps librarians and users handle tasks like book issue, return, catalog management, and membership records through a computerized system. The goal is to reduce manual work, increase accuracy, and provide faster service.

2. Objectives

Automate daily library tasks.

Maintain digital records of books and members.

Track issued, returned, and overdue books.

Reduce paperwork and human error.

Provide quick search and accessibility.

Improve the overall management process.

Technologies Used:

The Library Management System is developed using HTML, CSS, JavaScript for the front-end interface and Python (Flask) as the back-end framework. The data is stored in a MySQL database, and the system runs on Apache 
 using XAMPP. The project was developed using VS Code with GitHub for version contro
 
